HEADWORD: Staging
<hw>Sta"ging</hw> <pr>(st⟦amac⟧"j⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
structure of posts and boards for supporting workmen, etc., as in
building.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The business of running stagecoaches; also, the act
of journeying in stagecoaches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stagirite</ent>⟦br⟧
